EXPLAINATION OF THIS CODE IN THIS COMPONENT
We just pass the props we get from the redux-toolkit as a data.
"As we know, we fetch specific data from the database through a router linked to a unique ID.
This ID is passed to the backend API, which uses it to retrieve the corresponding post.
The API then sends an object containing all the details of the post, such as the title, image, date, tags,
and other relevant information. For example, if it retrieves the second post, all its details will be displayed in full view."
